# Known import-lint violations awaiting cleanup.
#
# Format: one `<rule_name> <file_path>` per line, no wildcards.
# Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#
# Any violation present in this file passes the lint; any
# violation NOT listed fails CI. The lint FAILS on new
# violations OR stale baseline entries, so the baseline shrinks
# monotonically as reworks land.
#
# ─── CURRENT STATE: 6 entries, all L/storage-below-compute ─────
#
# All legacy RPC-based per-source orchestration code was removed
# in PR 165d. New code must satisfy the rules in lint-imports.sh
# or explicitly justify an allowlist addition there. Adding an
# entry back to this file requires a PR description citing why
# the exception is temporary.
#
# L/storage-below-compute (D8 M0-1): the storage tier imports
# UPWARD into compute/sources because the persisted domain structs
# (supply.Supply, blend.PositionEvent, mev.StoredEvent, ...) and Sink
# interfaces are owned by upward packages. Grandfathered until the
# structs move to a neutral home (canonical / internal/domain);
# remove each line as its file's upward import goes away. Do NOT
# add new files to this list.
#
# 2026-07-10 (D8 M0-1 storage-layering move, ROADMAP #47): moved the
# plain persisted structs to the new internal/domain (zero-method
# shapes re-exported as transparent aliases from their origin
# package; method-bearing consumer.Event shapes — accounts.Observation,
# blend.PositionEvent/EmissionEvent/AdminEvent — re-declared as
# locally-defined types over the domain shape, since Go forbids
# methods on a type alias to a foreign type). This cleared 9 of the
# original 15 entries: account_observations.go, aggregates.go,
# blend_admin.go, blend_emissions.go, blend_positions.go,
# divergence_observations.go, mev.go, soroban_events.go,
# topic_samples.go. The remaining 6 could NOT move mechanically —
# each pulls in actual compute/policy logic, not just a persisted
# shape, so moving it would mean relocating business logic rather
# than a data struct:
#   - blend_pool_state_reader.go / blend_auctions.go: call blend's
#     scval-based ReserveData/PoolConfig decoders and
#     ParseReserveConfigMetadata; blend.ReserveConfig also crosses
#     into internal/api/v1 (lending.go) carrying a BorrowRate()
#     method, so it can't be decoupled from the blend package without
#     touching the API layer too.
#   - baseline.go: baseline.Baseline / baseline.MultiBaseline carry
#     ZScore()/HasAnyValid()/MaxZScore() methods AND are constructed
#     across internal/aggregate/baseline's refresh worker, not just
#     read/written by storage.
#   - freeze_events.go: anomaly.Decision's Class/Thresholds fields
#     pull in internal/aggregate/anomaly's classification + threshold
#     policy (Classifier, AssetClass), not a flat data shape.
#   - supply.go: supply.Supply / supply.Basis are constructed across
#     many internal/supply call sites (classic.go, crosscheck.go,
#     overlay.go, …); moving Basis (which carries a String() method)
#     would require touching every one of them.
#   - trades.go: calls aggregate.FiatProxy(...) and
#     external.Lookup(...)/external.FXSources() — genuine aggregator
#     / source-registry POLICY functions (CLAUDE.md: "Stablecoin
#     fiat-proxy is aggregator policy, not decoder policy"), not
#     persisted structs.
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/clickhouse/blend_pool_state_reader.go
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/timescale/baseline.go
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/timescale/blend_auctions.go
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/timescale/freeze_events.go
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/timescale/supply.go
L/storage-below-compute internal/storage/timescale/trades.go
